Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Resolving Ambiguities", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.985354791837942*^9, 
  3.985354796373461*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3b5e26b2-9076-4f0d-a92f-\
c04ae4451f48"],

Cell["\<\
As we can see from the answers above for part of the primaries the action of \
the defects is ambiguous and we really only know the trace. Yet we have a lot \
of data, perhaps enough to fully constrain the action on the primaries (up to \
a basis choice). To do this we will use fusion rules. These are highly \
constrained also simply by looking at the action in the nondegenerate \
primaries. Then we will search fusion rules for consistencies using a version \
of BFS.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.985354805231358*^9, 
  3.9853549465297213`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"e0649843-0a83-46b1-a791-\
a940ae635825"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Defect Manipulations", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9853551382637987`*^9, 
  3.985355145263522*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"eff918bb-fae2-4a9e-8c17-\
3090a18ffd57"],

Cell["\<\
Since we don\[CloseCurlyQuote]t need a really big matrix to store the action \
of the defects, we will instead opt to store them using a list of 1x1 and 2x2 \
matrices depending on which are ambiguous or not. So we can define an \
associative operation for the tensor product!!\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9853551464778633`*^9, 3.985355206816071*^9}, 
   3.985355267872313*^9},ExpressionUUID->"c7a72f28-611e-4ae3-992c-\
31dcef181568"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
   RowBox[{
   "Define", " ", "a", " ", "Defect", " ", "Fusion", " ", "Product", " ", 
    "Operation"}], " ", "*)"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"SetAttributes", "[", 
    RowBox[{"CircleTimes", ",", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"Flat", ",", "OneIdentity"}], "}"}]}], "]"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"a_", " ", "\[CircleTimes]", " ", "b_"}], ":=", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"Which", "[", 
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{
          RowBox[{"MatrixQ", "[", 
           RowBox[{"#", "[", 
            RowBox[{"[", "1", "]"}], "]"}], "]"}], "&&", 
          RowBox[{"MatrixQ", "[", 
           RowBox[{"#", "[", 
            RowBox[{"[", "2", "]"}], "]"}], "]"}]}], ",", 
         RowBox[{
          RowBox[{"#", "[", 
           RowBox[{"[", "1", "]"}], "]"}], ".", 
          RowBox[{"#", "[", 
           RowBox[{"[", "2", "]"}], "]"}]}], ",", "True", ",", 
         RowBox[{
          RowBox[{"#", "[", 
           RowBox[{"[", "1", "]"}], "]"}], "*", 
          RowBox[{"#", "[", 
           RowBox[{"[", "2", "]"}], "]"}]}]}], "]"}], "&"}], "/@", 
